structure.unit: B DISTRICTS FOR UNITED STATES HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES

law.catch_line: Division of Commonwealth into congressional districts.
law.text: The Commonwealth of Kentucky is divided into six (6) congressional districts as provided by KRS 118B.110 to 118B.160.
law.history: Created 1991 (2nd Extra. Sess.) Ky. Acts ch. 4, sec. 7, effective December 20, 1991.
